Source: Reuters Foundation AlertNet, Thu 12 Jan 2006 [edited]
<http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/L12586491.htm>

Turkey: H5N1 Virus Found in Lungs of the 3rd Fatal Case
---------------------------------------------------------
Tests have shown that the H5N1 avian influenza virus was present in
the lungs of the Turkish child who died last week and who had
originally tested negative for avian influenza virus infection, the
state Anatolian News Agency said on Thursday 12 Jan 2006.
The elder brother and sister of the 11 year-old patient were the 1st
confirmed cases of bird flu among human beings outside China and
Southeast Asia. [The elder brother died] on 1 Jan 2006, [and the
sister died] on 5 Jan 2006 and [this 3rd sibling] died on 6 Jan 2006
--
