Date: Thu 12 Jan 2006
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Yahoo News.com, Thu 12 Jan 2006 [edited]
<http://news.yahoo.com/s/ap/turkey_bird_flu;_ylt=AmtG.joC5U42HCifcEu7rXmTvyIi;_ylu=X3oDMTBiMW04NW9mBHNlYwMlJVRPUCUl>

Turkey: 2 More Human Cases of H5N1 Avian Influenza
-----------------------------------------------------
2 more Turks tested positive for the H5N1 avian influenza virus in
preliminary tests, the government said Thursday [12 Jan 2006],
bringing the total number of human infections to 18. Both victims
were from the stricken southeast, and had been in contact with
infected birds, officials said.
A Turkish lab also determined that last week's 3rd bird flu death
involved the H5N1 strain, the Health Ministry said, as authorities
stepped up the precautionary slaughter of thousands of birds in an
effort to keep the outbreak in check.
